# Walkthrough - Free CIBIL Check Implementation

I have successfully added the **Free CIBIL Check** feature to the Avani Loan Service platform. This feature is designed to generate leads while providing value to your customers with an instant credit score estimation and a professional PDF report.

## Changes Made

### 1. New "CIBIL Check" Page
- Created [CibilCheck.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20SERVICE%20FY%2026-27/src/pages/CibilCheck.jsx) and [CibilCheck.css](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20SERVICE%20FY%2026-27/src/pages/CibilCheck.css).
- Features a **3-step interactive form**:
    - **Step 1**: Personal Info (Name, PAN, Mobile, Email, Income, Age).
    - **Step 2**: OTP Verification (via EmailJS).
    - **Step 3**: Result Gauge & PDF Download.

### 2. Google Sheets Integration
- Created [googleSheets.js](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20SERVICE%20FY%2026-27/src/lib/googleSheets.js) to handle background data logging.
- When a user verifies their OTP, their data is automatically POSTed to your Google Sheets webhook.

### 3. PDF Report Generation
- Integrated `jspdf` to generate a branded "Credit Score Estimation Report" locally in the user's browser, which they can download immediately.

### 4. Navigation & Localization
- Registered the `/cibil-check` route in [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20SERVICE%20FY%2026-27/src/App.jsx).
- Updated the [Navbar](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20SERVICE%20FY%2026-27/src/components/Navbar.jsx) and added translations in [LanguageContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20SERVICE%20FY%2026-27/src/context/LanguageContext.jsx) for English, Marathi, and Hindi.

